This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language inference (NLI) and explores ways to mitigate bias in NLI models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training and evaluating models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the development of intelligent systems that can understand natural language. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
